    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available now is a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S, a definitive example of 90s Japanese engineering. This vehicle features the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, which maintains factory-spec compression across all rotor faces. The sequential transition remains seamless, indicating a vacuum system in peak operational health. The lightweight chassis is supported by its original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring the 50/50 weight distribution is fully leveraged. Every component, from the oil metering pump to the pre-control actuators, has been vetted for mechanical synchronicity. The exterior retains its factory luster with no signs of oxidation, while the interior is free of the typical plastics degradation or bolster wear found in lesser examples. This is a turnkey collector piece with zero deferred maintenance.",
